@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>

<div class="card p-4 shadow-sm">
    <p>
        At <strong>EventEase Venue Booking System</strong>, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security
        of all event, venue, and booking information managed within this platform.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h4>
    <p>
        The system stores essential data required for managing events and bookings, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Venue details (name, location, capacity, images)</li>
        <li>Event information (name, date, description)</li>
        <li>Booking details (dates, linked venues and events)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4">2. How Information is Used</h4>
    <p>
        This information is used strictly for:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Managing venue availability</li>
        <li>Preventing double bookings</li>
        <li>Tracking scheduled events</li>
        <li>Improving operational efficiency</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4">3. Data Security</h4>
    <p>
        All data is securely stored using cloud-based database services. Access to the system is restricted
        to authorised booking specialists and administrators only.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">4. Data Integrity</h4>
    <p>
        The system includes validation rules and constraints to ensure accuracy and consistency of booking data.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">5. Future Enhancements</h4>
    <p>
        As EventEase grows, additional security features and integrations with cloud services will be implemented
        to further enhance data protection and scalability.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">6. Contact</h4>
    <p>
        For any questions regarding this privacy policy, please contact the EventEase system administrator.
    </p>
</div>